  "elapsed_s": 88.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was pretty-- a rainy day, pretty much mud on the earth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went there with one very special feeling that I am arriving to the earth of my ancestors.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in despite very difficult conditions that I-- first of all, I went there to-- on kibbutz, working the earth for a number of months and learning the language that I find out that I don't know absolutely at all-- not very easy language.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I succeed to learn to write and read pretty fluently.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Until the moment in which I had the possibility to get connected again with the big cities, with Tel Aviv, and to make some connections that permitted me later on to make my auditions in which I was accepted as a member of the very famous-- worldly famous Israel Philharmonic Orchestra.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]-- this was my title.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was starting from the very back of this section of the second violin section.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I arrived very soon up to the first stand.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [SIGHS] I remained in Israel for a few years [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I find out that I'm able to participate in other audition, this allowing me not only to, to learn of some other very great masters, but would permit me to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] do something that I was, all my life, dreaming to be able to concertize.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This, in Israel, was very difficult, especially if you would like to live as a musician, do this concertize-- because the country is very small.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
